# ADR-001: Home SOC Project Philosophy
## Date

2026-07-16

## Context

The purpose of this project is to build a Home Security Operations Center while learning Linux, Docker, networking, monitoring, logging, automation, and cybersecurity.

Many homelabs become collections of software installed from tutorials without a clear understanding of why each service exists.

This project intentionally avoids that approach.

## Decision

The Home SOC will be developed according to the following principles.

- Understand before installing.
- Every service must solve a real problem.
- Build one layer at a time.
- Documentation is part of the project.
- Learn through experimentation.
- Break things. Fix them. Learn why.
- Security and ethics always come first.
- AI should assist investigation, not replace understanding.

## Consequences

This project may progress more slowly than other homelabs.

However, each component will be understood, documented, and intentionally integrated into the overall architecture.

The objective is not to build the largest lab.

The objective is to become a better engineer.
